    "title": {
        "rendered": "Howard Beckett"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p>Howard Beckett, a self-proclaimed socialist and trade unionist, has openly expressed his support for terrorist organizations like Hamas and Hezbollah. Both groups are responsible for violent attacks against civilians, targeting Israel with the goal of its destruction. Beckett\u2019s rhetoric consistently downplays the terrorism committed by these groups, instead focusing on harshly criticizing Israel\u2019s self-defense actions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Through his social media posts, Beckett spreads dangerous narratives that not only vilify Israel but also provide sympathy for groups that carry out acts of terror. By calling Israel\u2019s defensive actions \u201cterrorism\u201d and failing to acknowledge the brutality of Hamas and Hezbollah, Beckett\u2019s language mirrors the propaganda used by these groups to justify their violent campaigns. His refusal to condemn the clear-cut terrorism of these organizations highlights his alignment with their goals and tactics.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Beckett&#8217;s support for these terrorists is clear, and those who follow him or adopt his views risk being seen as sympathizers of terrorism. His ongoing defense of groups that murder innocent civilians and his inflammatory attacks on Israel only serve to legitimize these organizations\u2019 violent agendas. Anyone aligning themselves with Beckett is effectively aligning with the very groups that seek to destroy Israel and destabilize the region.</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
        "rendered": "<p>he openly supports terrorists! If you follow him, you might also be a terrorist sympathizer</p>\n",
